513
00:40:03,410 --> 00:40:06,240
Doesn't this sound too familiar?

514
00:40:07,360 --> 00:40:12,360
In the end, you'll take the money what's left of the business. You pull all funds pretending to develop new projects.

515
00:40:12,360 --> 00:40:14,750
That sounds like you'll take the money and run.

516
00:40:14,750 --> 00:40:16,210
That will never happen.

517
00:40:16,210 --> 00:40:18,680
We're currently in development for the new game.

518
00:40:18,680 --> 00:40:22,510
I can guarantee an effective increase in revenue once we release internationally.

519
00:40:22,510 --> 00:40:24,520
You'll give up on stable income

520
00:40:24,520 --> 00:40:27,930
and you'll risk it all on a dangerous bet. What is that new project anyway?

521
00:40:27,930 --> 00:40:29,510
I can't tell you that.

522
00:40:29,510 --> 00:40:33,460
It's connected to the management strategy. It's confidential.

523
00:40:33,460 --> 00:40:37,220
Confidential? You don't have to keep it a secret from us shareholders.

524
00:40:37,220 --> 00:40:40,670
Not long ago, we had an incident where our proposal was leaked.

525
00:40:40,670 --> 00:40:44,410
Since then, we decided to have only the strategic planning team to share the proposals.

526
00:40:44,410 --> 00:40:47,700
That is our policy.

527
00:40:49,100 --> 00:40:54,090
You expect me to believe that? Are you sure you have a plan?

528
00:40:54,090 --> 00:41:00,110
I apologize, but the only thing I can reveal to you is that we're currently developing new projects.

529
00:41:00,110 --> 00:41:02,910
<i>Let's be honest here, CEO Ahn!</i>

530
00:41:02,910 --> 00:41:07,970
It's only been a month since you started. You're telling me you're developing a new game that will turn the table?

531
00:41:07,970 --> 00:41:10,540
You think that makes sense?

532
00:41:12,570 --> 00:41:13,580
We're currently developing.

533
00:41:13,580 --> 00:41:17,500
So, you should explain to us properly what you're currently developing!

534
00:41:17,500 --> 00:41:20,400
I've never seen CEO Jo so angry like that.

535
00:41:20,400 --> 00:41:22,420
It's understandable.

536
00:41:22,420 --> 00:41:27,070
He was told that his baby Pigwar was fold off and we're holding someone else's baby.

537
00:41:27,070 --> 00:41:33,130
But no matter how angry he gets, the agenda will pass regardless.

538
00:41:33,130 --> 00:41:35,790
I just feel sorry for him.

539
00:41:35,790 --> 00:41:41,860
No. CEO Jo already knows that he can't stop it.

540
00:41:41,860 --> 00:41:45,990
That's not why he's getting so angry like that right now.

541
00:41:45,990 --> 00:41:47,800
Then what?

542
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:50,270
They keep a record of the meeting in the minutes.

543
00:41:50,270 --> 00:41:56,230
They have an obligation to record everything and share with everyone.

544
00:41:56,230 --> 00:41:59,710
He wants to make the issue public.

545
00:41:59,710 --> 00:42:03,720
Public? What's next then?

546
00:42:04,880 --> 00:42:07,670
If you don't have any plans for the next product,

547
00:42:07,670 --> 00:42:10,680
I charge CEO Ahn Dan Te with malicious and risky business management,

548
00:42:10,680 --> 00:42:15,360
the outflow of funds by selling IP, and breach of duty.

549
00:42:23,690 --> 00:42:25,870
We got sucked into this.

550
00:42:26,960 --> 00:42:27,670
Delete it from the record.

551
00:42:27,670 --> 00:42:30,370
Don't miss a word.

552
00:42:30,370 --> 00:42:31,770
Yes.

553
00:42:31,770 --> 00:42:33,780
Look, look, take it away and look.

554
00:42:33,780 --> 00:42:36,450
Let's see if you recorded everything.

555
00:42:36,450 --> 00:42:38,470
Aren't you an employee here?

556
00:42:38,470 --> 00:42:40,220
I'm a new recruit.

557
00:42:40,220 --> 00:42:43,010
You should have a professional transcriptionist.

558
00:42:43,010 --> 00:42:46,190
You're in it together playing games with us?

559
00:42:46,190 --> 00:42:48,790
Look at this terrible company. From the get-go,

560
00:42:48,790 --> 00:42:51,360
how dare you try to mock the shareholders?

561
00:42:51,360 --> 00:42:56,530
08A1907725.

562
00:42:56,530 --> 00:42:58,570
Take it out.

563
00:42:58,570 --> 00:43:00,300
Yes, sir.

564
00:43:07,130 --> 00:43:08,660
For transparency in our records,

565
00:43:08,660 --> 00:43:11,320
We hired a newbie who has

566
00:43:11,320 --> 00:43:13,460
a national certification for transcription.

567
00:43:13,460 --> 00:43:18,280
Everything is being recorded. So please don't worry.

568
00:43:21,540 --> 00:43:24,220
<i>Certification</i>

569
00:43:24,220 --> 00:43:25,460
<i>Application</i>

570
00:43:25,460 --> 00:43:27,450
<i>Certification: Transcriptionist</i>

571
00:43:27,450 --> 00:43:29,800
Are you sure it's legit?

572
00:43:29,800 --> 00:43:32,770
We'll check everything in the end.

573
00:43:32,770 --> 00:43:37,270
There's no point. How much longer do you think your lies will last?

574
00:43:37,270 --> 00:43:39,110
You should know this, too.

575
00:43:39,110 --> 00:43:43,960
What I say is also being recorded in the minutes.

576
00:43:43,960 --> 00:43:48,390
CEO Jo Tae Goo, you were fired from Joybuster, right?

577
00:43:48,390 --> 00:43:51,020
You want to damage my reputation?

578
00:43:51,020 --> 00:43:54,720
Did you get fired for lying all the time?

579
00:43:54,720 --> 00:43:55,980
I don't lie.

580
00:43:55,980 --> 00:43:57,710
Then what is your standard for lying?

581
00:43:57,710 --> 00:43:58,700
You don't know?

582
00:43:58,700 --> 00:44:01,810
If you can't keep a promise, does that make it a lie?

583
00:44:01,810 --> 00:44:05,200
A company always announces its plans for the future.

584
00:44:05,200 --> 00:44:07,220
It just hasn't come to fruition yet.

585
00:44:07,220 --> 00:44:08,820
You're saying you only laid out the plan?

586
00:44:08,820 --> 00:44:10,890
Is it any different if I do it?

587
00:44:10,890 --> 00:44:16,490
Did you manage to keep your plans well to drive it to the ground?

588
00:44:17,090 --> 00:44:19,130
You can't take me down with you like that.

589
00:44:19,130 --> 00:44:23,470
I am trying to get you to stand with me. But I'm not saying we should both go down.

590
00:44:23,470 --> 00:44:29,310
I'm saying this because I believe you didn't intend to lie either.

591
00:44:29,310 --> 00:44:33,850
A company's plan is a decision made for the company to survive.

592
00:44:33,850 --> 00:44:35,720
This is the truth.

593
00:44:35,720 --> 00:44:37,850
You asked what my standard for lying is, right?

594
00:44:37,850 --> 00:44:45,080
It's simple. If none of the employees working here believe you, it means it's a lie.

595
00:44:59,930 --> 00:45:06,700
Do you all believe CEO Ahn's words?

596
00:45:22,990 --> 00:45:24,890
See?

597
00:45:26,970 --> 00:45:29,580
You can't say a thing even if you're reported.

598
00:45:55,350 --> 00:46:00,520
I'll say an honest word about the new product development.

599
00:46:00,520 --> 00:46:03,810
Fine. Come clean if you got caught.

600
00:46:03,810 --> 00:46:09,510
Shutting down the project, selling Pigwar, and the opposition from the shareholders for canceling the publisher.

601
00:46:09,510 --> 00:46:10,900
I expected all that.

602
00:46:10,900 --> 00:46:14,710
Of course, I considered the fact that you'll doubt the validity of the new product.

603
00:46:14,710 --> 00:46:19,420
However, what's important to us is a platform for us to jump off of.

604
00:46:19,420 --> 00:46:21,370
We'll work on that platform first...

605
00:46:21,370 --> 00:46:25,740
Don't bother with all the spiel. Cut to the chase.

606
00:46:25,740 --> 00:46:28,630
I thought you liked that.

607
00:46:29,370 --> 00:46:33,020
Do you have a new product in mind or not?

608
00:46:34,060 --> 00:46:36,170
Do you or don't you?

609
00:46:45,350 --> 00:46:46,810
Currently...

610
00:46:46,810 --> 00:46:49,950
Don't drag this out and just tell them.

611
00:46:52,220 --> 00:46:54,970
It's so frustrating. What are you doing?

612
00:46:59,350 --> 00:47:03,170
I'm Shin Yeon Hwa, Planning Team Leader.

613
00:47:03,170 --> 00:47:05,460
Stay out of it.

614
00:47:06,620 --> 00:47:10,870
Since developing new product is my job, I can speak to you myself, right?

615
00:47:10,870 --> 00:47:14,100
Sure. You go ahead.

616
00:47:15,690 --> 00:47:17,080
Please step aside.

617
00:47:17,080 --> 00:47:20,840
That's right. The person in charge wants to reveal it herself.

618
00:47:20,840 --> 00:47:23,640
CEO Ahn, step aside if you don't have anything to say.

619
00:47:23,640 --> 00:47:25,890
That's right. Move. Step aside.

620
00:47:25,890 --> 00:47:29,160
Take his mic away.

621
00:47:41,290 --> 00:47:43,880
Okay, Yeon Hwa. Speak.

622
00:47:43,880 --> 00:47:46,770
Do you or don't you?

623
00:47:46,770 --> 00:47:49,400
We don't.

624
00:47:49,400 --> 00:47:51,600
That's right.

625
00:47:51,600 --> 00:47:53,440
There's no way you have it.

626
00:47:53,440 --> 00:47:58,480
To come up with new product funds, he sold off Pigwar.

627
00:47:58,480 --> 00:48:05,270
I had to stand back and watch since I'm just an employee. But I can't stand back any longer.

628
00:48:05,270 --> 00:48:08,180
I'll tell you everything.

629
00:48:08,180 --> 00:48:09,800
Good job!

630
00:48:09,800 --> 00:48:12,830
Okay. Tell us everything now.

631
00:48:12,830 --> 00:48:15,470
We have nothing here.

632
00:48:15,470 --> 00:48:19,840
It's just an empty office.

633
00:48:19,840 --> 00:48:23,800
So, it makes me think every morning when I come to work.

634
00:48:23,800 --> 00:48:25,730
It must be difficult for you.

635
00:48:25,730 --> 00:48:31,260
This is so fun.

636
00:48:32,130 --> 00:48:34,830
Fun?

637
00:48:35,480 --> 00:48:38,730
You're pissed off at the company and want to throw thinner (sounds like fun) at it, right?

638
00:48:38,730 --> 00:48:45,880
The excitement of filling out the blanks one day at a time. Don't you know?

639
00:48:47,120 --> 00:48:51,170
It sure is fun. Just like this storage walls.

640
00:48:51,170 --> 00:48:55,760
Should I tell you about our new project? Nothing.

641
00:48:55,760 --> 00:48:59,120
Of course, it's just not in a physical form yet.

642
00:48:59,120 --> 00:49:05,580
But in the planning team's brain, including mine, it's already completed.

643
00:49:05,580 --> 00:49:07,910
Bring me the proposal.

644
00:49:07,910 --> 00:49:11,780
He already said it's confidential and we're working on it.

645
00:49:11,780 --> 00:49:16,760
CEO Jo, aren't you aware of the importance of security more than anyone else?

646
00:49:21,610 --> 00:49:22,600
Yeon Hwa, what are you doing?

647
00:49:22,600 --> 00:49:26,010
Two years ago, a competitor of ours

648
00:49:26,010 --> 00:49:29,960
released a similar item and we took the loss.

649
00:49:29,960 --> 00:49:33,850
You had to give up on the development balance we were owed and shut it down.

650
00:49:33,850 --> 00:49:40,340
Why? Objectively speaking, their game was upgraded better than ours.

651
00:49:40,340 --> 00:49:43,390
In conclusion, I took all the responsibility and stepped down.

652
00:49:43,390 --> 00:49:44,340
So CEO Ahn should also...

653
00:49:44,340 --> 00:49:46,700
I'm not talking about your fault.

654
00:49:46,700 --> 00:49:50,410
We just don't want to repeat the same mistake.

655
00:49:50,410 --> 00:49:52,400
If you're trying to get past this by saying it's confidential...

656
00:49:52,400 --> 00:49:56,800
No, if we pass this agenda and close the meeting,

657
00:49:56,800 --> 00:50:03,030
I'll brief you on the new product separately without having to worry about the minutes.

658
00:50:03,030 --> 00:50:05,100
What do you think?

659
00:50:12,230 --> 00:50:16,330
You're on his team now.

660
00:50:16,330 --> 00:50:19,180
We're on the same team.

661
00:50:19,180 --> 00:50:21,470
Yeon Hwa.

662
00:50:21,470 --> 00:50:26,510
Joybuster was always on the same team.

663
00:50:26,510 --> 00:50:31,330
You too, CEO Jo, and also shareholders.

664
00:50:31,330 --> 00:50:34,940
We're all on the same team, aren't we?

665
00:50:36,820 --> 00:50:38,960
No, you can't.

666
00:50:38,960 --> 00:50:41,750
What Ms. Shin is suggesting isn't what the company desires.

667
00:50:41,750 --> 00:50:45,500
We can share the info with no one else except for the development team.

668
00:50:45,500 --> 00:50:46,960
CEO!

669
00:50:46,960 --> 00:50:51,860
We even had a proposal leak the other day. How can we trust him?

670
00:50:51,860 --> 00:50:56,500
How can we? We've known him longer than you.

671
00:50:56,500 --> 00:51:00,040
Much longer and much closer.

672
00:51:00,040 --> 00:51:03,830
CEO Jo Tae Goo will never...

673
00:51:04,810 --> 00:51:09,350
make the wrong decision.

674
00:51:23,330 --> 00:51:25,270
Fine.

675
00:51:26,200 --> 00:51:33,600
CEO Jo, would you like to hear our report before you leave?

676
00:51:37,530 --> 00:51:42,200
CEO, we're busy people, too.

677
00:51:42,200 --> 00:51:46,220
That's right, CEO Jo. Decide what you'll do.

678
00:51:46,220 --> 00:51:50,890
Turn over the table with these kids and wake them up!

679
00:51:50,890 --> 00:51:55,980
I'll pass this agenda.

680
00:52:24,730 --> 00:52:25,930
Chairman, sir.

681
00:52:25,930 --> 00:52:28,040
Do you agree to pass?

682
00:52:29,020 --> 00:52:30,060
I agree.

683
00:52:30,060 --> 00:52:32,170
- Agreed!
- Agreed!

684
00:52:32,170 --> 00:52:34,110
- Agreed!
- Agreed!

685
00:52:34,110 --> 00:52:36,130
Agreed.

686
00:52:36,130 --> 00:52:42,020
The agenda has passed with a unanimous vote from the shareholders present.

687
00:52:42,020 --> 00:52:49,040
The 2019 Joybuster Regular Shareholders Meeting is adjourned.

688
00:53:16,000 --> 00:53:20,700
It's a new innovative product that emphasizes camaraderie among the users.

689
00:53:20,700 --> 00:53:25,860
We've pulled all the technical and design capabilities that developed and managed Pigwar.

690
00:53:25,860 --> 00:53:28,160
It will be a relentless project.

691
00:53:28,160 --> 00:53:30,260
That's all.

692
00:53:37,140 --> 00:53:38,200
It's not our style.

693
00:53:38,200 --> 00:53:40,170
That approach is intentional.

694
00:53:40,170 --> 00:53:44,740
I hope the users also feel that it's different from the usual Joybuster style.

695
00:53:44,740 --> 00:53:48,190
What's Joybuster's branding identity?

696
00:53:48,190 --> 00:53:50,730
"Bringing happiness to the world."

697
00:53:50,730 --> 00:53:56,140
It may be different from the style of the games we've produced thus far. But it doesn't mean we've changed.

698
00:53:56,140 --> 00:54:01,560
Another words, our branding identity hasn't changed.

699
00:54:03,170 --> 00:54:05,360
Whose idea is this?

700
00:54:12,490 --> 00:54:16,440
Joybuster's idea.

701
00:54:29,670 --> 00:54:32,230
Why didn't you work like this when I was here?

702
00:54:32,230 --> 00:54:34,420
This is great!

703
00:54:34,420 --> 00:54:36,950
Great! Great! Great!

704
00:54:36,950 --> 00:54:38,470
Great!

705
00:54:38,470 --> 00:54:41,150
Push this forward just like this.

706
00:54:41,150 --> 00:54:45,320
If there's any shareholder who interferes with this, I'll roll up my sleeves

707
00:54:45,320 --> 00:54:48,170
and convince them by showing up at their house.

708
00:54:48,170 --> 00:54:49,720
Got it?

709
00:54:49,720 --> 00:54:51,480
Great. That's it!

710
00:54:51,480 --> 00:54:53,240
Great, great, great!

711
00:54:53,240 --> 00:54:55,520
Great, great!

712
00:55:01,050 --> 00:55:02,000
CEO.

713
00:55:02,000 --> 00:55:05,170
Good job. You're good at your job!

714
00:55:05,170 --> 00:55:07,610
You should've been a team leader sooner.

715
00:55:07,610 --> 00:55:09,430
I'm sorry about earlier.

716
00:55:09,430 --> 00:55:13,330
Were you sad because I didn't side with you?

717
00:55:13,330 --> 00:55:15,420
No way.

718
00:55:15,420 --> 00:55:17,230
I feel bad.

719
00:55:35,380 --> 00:55:38,770
What's your real reason for coming here?

720
00:55:38,770 --> 00:55:41,770
I got nothing to do at home.

721
00:55:41,770 --> 00:55:44,810
You weren't dreaming of conquering?

722
00:55:45,500 --> 00:55:47,940
Could be.

723
00:55:47,940 --> 00:55:54,500
Selling the company at such a low price. Did you anticipate this situation?

724
00:55:55,550 --> 00:55:57,960
I can't see the future that well.

725
00:55:57,960 --> 00:56:03,800
I understand that NexViper showed greater interest with a better offer.

726
00:56:03,800 --> 00:56:09,050
I wanted to know what your real reason is for handing over the company to us.

727
00:56:09,050 --> 00:56:11,400
I was so angry.

728
00:56:12,790 --> 00:56:18,170
Somehow, we became their subcontractor.

729
00:56:18,170 --> 00:56:21,900
And the company faltered because we didn't follow their order.

730
00:56:22,870 --> 00:56:26,240
That's not why I had started this company.

731
00:56:26,240 --> 00:56:32,050
I started it to make the game I, I mean, we wanted to make.

732
00:56:33,770 --> 00:56:37,870
I completely understand how you feel.

733
00:56:40,160 --> 00:56:41,890
CEO Ahn.

734
00:56:42,720 --> 00:56:45,060
I don't care what kind of position it is.

735
00:56:45,060 --> 00:56:49,260
Can I continue to work here?

736
00:56:57,050 --> 00:57:02,390
Prohibited to work in the same market within three years. Did you forget the contract?

737
00:57:02,390 --> 00:57:03,900
I want to make games.

738
00:57:03,900 --> 00:57:07,930
You're at fault for the past failed management.

739
00:57:07,930 --> 00:57:10,930
You should stop working with games.

740
00:57:11,880 --> 00:57:16,580
But instead, I'll ask you for a favor.

741
00:57:16,580 --> 00:57:17,420
A favor?

742
00:57:17,420 --> 00:57:22,410
You may have failed the company, but you've come all this way focused on games only all your life.

743
00:57:22,410 --> 00:57:24,960
I don't think you're a failure at that.

744
00:57:24,960 --> 00:57:31,630
At the least, I can tell that by looking at the employees who protect and follow you.

745
00:57:31,630 --> 00:57:32,580
CEO Ahn.

746
00:57:32,580 --> 00:57:36,610
If I lack anything, as a life sunbae who has lived in the world of games,

747
00:57:36,610 --> 00:57:42,030
I ask for your uncensored advice and criticisms.

748
00:57:43,900 --> 00:57:46,090
I ask of you.

749
00:57:52,190 --> 00:57:53,210
Is it too much?

750
00:57:53,210 --> 00:57:54,860
Yes.

751
00:58:09,800 --> 00:58:14,980
Last time when you came by the monastery, I didn't tell you why I hired you, huh?

752
00:58:14,980 --> 00:58:18,560
You said you just hired me trying to be cool.

753
00:58:21,110 --> 00:58:25,640
I thought you'd fight well in my place.

754
00:58:26,440 --> 00:58:30,510
For Joybuster. Just like today.

755
00:58:31,180 --> 00:58:33,280
CEO...

756
00:58:35,050 --> 00:58:39,470
She's fighting very well with me thanks to you who hired her.

757
00:58:40,330 --> 00:58:42,200
Do I fight for no reason?

758
00:58:42,200 --> 00:58:45,100
You make up reasons to fight.

759
00:58:46,180 --> 00:58:48,530
See? How can I not get upset?

760
00:58:48,530 --> 00:58:51,020
Just think he's expressing his interest in you.

761
00:58:51,020 --> 00:58:55,050
Celebrities say malicious comments are better than no comments.

762
00:58:56,920 --> 00:58:59,270
You two have great chemistry.

763
00:58:59,270 --> 00:59:01,160
CEO!

764
00:59:02,500 --> 00:59:03,800
Am I overdoing it here?

765
00:59:03,800 --> 00:59:05,410
Yes.

766
00:59:07,300 --> 00:59:09,360
Goodbye, CEO!

767
00:59:09,360 --> 00:59:11,860
- Bye!
